Key Match Events: Wyatt Langford smashed a walk-off grand slam in the ninth inning, lifting the Texas Rangers to a 7-4 win over the New York Yankees.
Rangers rookie reliever Walter Pennington earned his first major league win.
Josh Jung hit a solo home run and went 2-for-3 with two RBIs.
Anthony Volpe went 2-for-4 with two RBIs and a run for the Yankees.
New York starter Carlos Rodon struck out 11 and held the Rangers to one hit through six innings.
